## NDR Logo Assets (Do Not Approximate)

Never describe or invent the NDR logo from memory. Always pass the actual logo files as reference_images and instruct the prompt to reproduce them from the reference.

- **Full wordmark**: `/Users/kelly.cruz/Documents/devRoot/BTNDRMASTER/NDR-FRONTENDS/BTAssist/PMDEMOASSIST/brandguide/ndrlogo.svg`
  - "NATIONAL DEBT RELIEF" in navy #1F2147, red flag/banner #A31921, decorative stars, "DEBT RELIEF" subtitle, horizontal rule
- **Shield only**: `/Users/kelly.cruz/Documents/devRoot/BTNDRMASTER/NDR-FRONTENDS/BTAssist/PMDEMOASSIST/brandguide/registered-trademark-shield-ndr.svg`
  - Shield shape in navy #1F2147 with red #A31921 flag accent and stars, registered trademark symbol

When generating cover slides or branded images that require the NDR logo, include BOTH logo files in reference_images and use the phrase: "Reproduce the NDR logo exactly as shown in the reference images" in the prompt.

## Prompt Construction Pattern

When building a Nano Banana prompt for this character, always include these elements in order:

- Art style: "anime/manga cel-shaded illustration style"
- Gender: "female character" — always specify, do NOT generate as male
- Hair: "bright spiky red hair swept upward with a red headband"
- Face: "sharp anime-style eyes with feminine features, slender athletic build"
- Goggles: "steampunk-style goggles pushed up on their forehead with navy blue frames"
- Outfit: "white labcoat with red accent trim, open in front showing a red necktie over dark shirt, black pants, dark navy combat boots with red laces"
- Badge: "single lanyard employee badge around the neck showing only the NDR shield logo (navy blue shield with red flag accent and small stars, no text)"
- Pose: describe the pose appropriate to the variant
- Weapon (action only): "large dark metallic rocket launcher over one shoulder with red accent highlights"
- Colors: "deep navy blue (#1F2147) and flag red (#A31921) color palette, white background"
- Constraint: "no duplicate badges, no extra text on the badge, single lanyard badge only"

